76561198064488597,Not Recommended,320340,28296212,"Posted: 10 December, 2016",all,Psyckosama,"This is going to sound odd, but this is a good game. It's frustrating, but fun. Kind of like an old Nintendo game in some ways. And in some ways, that's part of the problem, because while its fun and frustrating, it's also lacking in polish in many areas.There's a some big annoyances with this game and the problem is they're never going to be fixed. The team is small, has moved onto other projects, and the worst part is it's not really their fault. This game runs on the Havok ""Project Anarchy"" Engine which had its support cut late 2015. What this means is updating the game is very difficult and many stability issues that might pop up in the future will probably be impossible to fix.That said, its still fun, but it's not $15 dollars fun. It's more $5 dollars fun when you consider what you see is what you get. Should they drop the price, I'll recommend it. But for now, wait for a Steam Sale."
