,Recommended,320340,12685942,"Posted: 29 October, 2014",all,Dogmaticus,"This is one hell of a game already, and I can't wait to see it develop further, but... let's start with the begining.Cosmonautica is a unique combination of many genres. You need to manage the space and modules on your ship, you need to hire/fire/promote (or simply: manage!) your crew, get missions, trade, think, if needed - fight. All the things you do have even visual impact on your ship (which can currently be customised in terms of what facilities it has, where they are placed, but also in terms of visuals, and more features such as customizable crew uniforms are coming!), which isI' great, and reminds me of the games from my childhood in early 90's.As said - it does remind me of the games from my childhood - it combines the traits of sea faring games with the fun factor of management sims such as Airline Tycoon, and all that with a pinch of interstellar adventure.. it's almost as if Privateer met Airline Tycoon, with just a bit of Pirates! for the taste ;).I'm really impressed with this game, and I only started playing it. I believe it's definitely worth 10 Euro to pay for, as it's already very enjoyable.So... don't hesitate, buy it, and have fun!"
