76561198054497740,Recommended,320340,15628297,"Posted: 30 April, 2015",all,phantomFractal,"I am really enjoying this addictive little space sim.  The atmosphere is relaxing and casual. There are a lot of bugs still as this is in early access and the game crashes every so often (sometimes frequently). That being said I have enjoyed it thoroughly in early access. I recommend it to anyone who gets in the mood to play games like The Sims or Banished as both of these games are addictive, relaxing, and have a respectively low learning curve as compared to some more complicated city builders out there. Right now it is enjoyable enough discovering the best strategy to earn more income to upgrade your ship, give crew members raises, or hire more crew members. As they gain experience they have increasing needs beyond the basic fulfillment of hunger, sleep, hygiene, toileting. If they are unhappy or do not have their needs met they will become sick and unable to work. It oftentimes becomes a balance to build items/rooms that meet their needs vs. items/rooms that can generate more income.  More specific ways to generate income beyond general trading of items from one planet to another include: delivering passengers planet to planet, smuggling of illegal goods/persons, and space combat. These are some of the dynamics you will find as far as gameplay is concerned. I look forward to more content in the future."
