76561198050433002,Recommended,320340,17463724,"Posted: 9 August, 2015",all,rcjenn40,"First came The Sims, then Sims Medieval, and now it's...SIMS IN SPACE!Or at least that's what you'll instantly think when you start this game.It's a relaxing, casual space-faring game of trading, building skills, taking care of the needs of your crew and optional combat missions.You don't need to fight at all if you don't want to, but as of the time of this review, the Easy Combat mission, which constantly gets offered at various stations is a veritable quick and easy ATM machine to print money for ships and upgrades.Looking past that one flaw...or feature, depending on how you look at it...the game will easily fill the occassional itch of armchair space captains who just want to wander space completely on their own terms and play style. It has both a storymode and sandbox mode, and all of the ports of call have missions to undertake if you feel so inclined. If not, then just fill you holds with cigarettes and beer and head out.Has a multitude of solar systems to discover, quite a few ship layouts in three basic styles; trader, cruise ship, or warship and many room types and upgrades.All in all, a fun, relaxing, casual space-faring romp for those players who just want to play the way they personally enjoy, and really, what can be better than that?"
