76561198005403826,Recommended,320340,15510837,"Posted: 23 April, 2015",all,RogueM99,"To be simple, I love the game in it's current state. Even with all of the issues and the crashes. Iron those puppies out and you have me hooked for a long while. The description and videos you see will give you most of your value in whether to purchase or not. Gameplay lived up to the hype I created for it after finding this gem. Hire your own pilot, janitor, engineer and researcher. Buy and sell goods that can be transported from planet to planet. Manage your ship or the ship will manage you out of a job and into a game over. Take risks with missions in transporting goods that aren't quite listed on the legal side of the law. Don't get caught or you'll pay a hefty fine. Hopefully you have the money to bribe or pay the fine. If not, good luck building it back up again.You can add ""modules"" to the interior of your ship so that it is fitted with the right amount of crew space, cargo holds and necessities to control your space place. Change the name of your ship and the varying color scheme. Change the crews uniform color as well while you are at it.Overall I'm very happy I made this purchase and have supported what seems to be a very well rounded group of indie developers who are doing their best to deliver what was promised. I hope somebody finds this information useful.***UPDATE****After a few updates the game was running much better. Crashes were less often, almost non-existent for me.The problems I began to notice over a longer period of time playing related to the buying and selling of goods from planet/station to planet/station. It was very rare in the first solar system phase that I was able to make a profit on selling goods I purchased at locations that needed that maeterial. This was the biggest disappointment for me. The Contracts were interesting and had some thought put into them. However, managing the location you were headed, how long it would take to get there, how much money you have and whether you can afford to pay your staff, as well as what time limits you have on the contracts you currently have makes it very difficult to plan out a path to make the Contracts truly valuable.I've never had a very successful time during space battles. I haven't played a single save to the point where I am able to get more highly skilled shipmates to see if that makes the space battles less of a chore. Battles don't occur frequently however.Overall this game is interesting but I want to see more contracts made available per station, some login put into the contracts time required to complete, ways to truly build up a profit by buying goods at low cost and selling them at a high payout dependant on needs per location.What I want is a game where I can build my own spaceship, manage my crew, modify the functions of my space ship as to whether it's a space ferry, cargo ship, mercenary, or smuggler. This game has that potential but needs more fine tuning."
