76561197989769494,Recommended,320340,17259720,"Posted: 27 July, 2015",all,Citizen 246,"From what I could glean off of the images, video, and other media available of Cosmonautica, it immiediately appeared as though it was a Spaceship management game of it's own style. Quite fortunately, my interpetation of what I saw was wholly correct.The designers of the game did an excellant job of not taking themselves, and their creation -too- seriously. the game is quite fun and addictive, but tends to be somewhat easy to burn yourself out on. While there is alot of content in the game already, before long, you'll have an outlook of ""Been there, done that."" at just about every task, oppurtunity, and occurence that comes your way. I've hit that point several times now after a few hours of gameplay each run through, and yet, I can't keep from continuing to play it. The music is groovy, carying a melody and flow to it that's likely nearly unknown to most of this generation's avid gamers, while the graphics are soft enough to run smoothly on even most low-end graphic specs, without looking remotely distasteful.Speaking as someone who's dumped alot of their personal time into Space-based management games(E.G. FTL, Kerbal Space Program, Mars Expedition, Starbound, Lunar Flight, X3, etc.) , this game is a very refreshing change of pace. If you're into any of the games mentioned above, but still on the fence about getting this one, I say go ahead.While it isn't done yet, the devs are pretty active on it's improvement, and have thus far shown that they pay attention and respond to the problems/suggestions of their customer base. To me, that's a critical factor for any Early Access Game.For what I look for in games, I'd give it a 8/10. Consider the two missing points room to grow, haha."
