76561198019973580,Recommended,320340,17704380,"Posted: 24 August, 2015",all,Sutekh,"I see the haters have come out of the woodwork. This was my first foray into space trading games and I very much enjoyed it. There were minor issues here and there (pathfinding, combat), but I was making too much (virtual) dough to really care.Pros:1) This game works well as a beginner's guide to space trading games. IMO there's a lot of tedium in trading games that Cosmonautica does away with and it lets you figure out fairly quickly how to make money.2) Three different ways to play: trader, passenger ship, pirate. For each play style, you'll be looking for different crew complements, prioritizing different tech, and balancing crew comforts vs availability of rooms. There's also a campaign so that stretches out play time for a bit.3) Ship customization. Do you want to max out carrying capacity while minimizing creature comforts to ensure maximum profit? Do you want to get a mix of cargo containers and passenger seats to do a mix of missions?Cons:1) Game will crash every 20 min or so. This is extremely annoying, but the auto save sort of mitigates this. There's no rhyme or reason to why it'll crash: sometimes I'm clicking on a station or I'm moving some crew members around.2) There's really no end game. You can buy the most expensive ships fairly quickly and after that there's little reason to keep playing."
