76561198006932347,Not Recommended,320340,17688314,"Posted: 23 August, 2015",all,koro,"I wanted to like this game, I really did. But after putting a few hours into the campaign I just can't recommend this.To start with, the research tree is horrible. You have to research the middle and outer rings to get to more planets in the same system. Why? Does my ship not have sensors? Do the stations not have starcharts?The room research is the worst offender though. At some point, your crew is going to want shower. You have to research a bathrrom with a shower. So let me understand, we know how to build spacefaring ships but don't know how to include a shower in the bathroom? Or a kitchen, medbay, gym, etc. In my opinion, this is just stupid. All of the rooms should have been unlocked from the start and research should have been applied to upgrading the efficiency of your existing rooms.Next is travelling between planets. The pathfinding is mediocre at best and will do things that make no sense. I've had it where planets that were in the same wedge (think of the solar system divided into slices, like a pizza) but only 2 orbits apart take 7 days to travel...all because the pathfinding decided that my ship would fly counter-clockwise around the entire system instead of just doing a straight shot to the planet. Oddly enough, exiting the game and then reloading the save made the game recalculate the path to a still inefficient 4.5 days.Combat. I tried it once. On a 1 skull rated difficulty. Which turned into an utter failure. The lack of ability to manually control your flight path is a terrible decision. It would've been ok if there were more choices available to you. Right now, all you can do is close the distance, fly circles around your enemy (doesn't work well enough), and flee. Oh...there's an evade button you can use but all that does is move the ship to the side briefly. Which doesn't work well.The game has potential but in its current state, that's all I can say about it. Wait for demo to try it out or for the price to be slashed during a sale if you're interested."
