76561197987153183,Recommended,320340,17157405,"Posted: 21 July, 2015",all,Rysq,"The answer to your question is yes, you should buy it.The only poor reveiws I see are morons who think this game is trying to be something they have already played. ie: ""its not FTL"".Well thank god, FTL was good, but if it was another FTL, I wouldnt be interested. So go play bloody FTL then....I rather like that this game has its own identity, its not trying to ripoff anything. One can state some aspects have similarities to other games, but then again the market of games is so broad, you can make a 8 bit pixel game in html and it will have similarities to a great many other games. So if your only frame of reference is other games you have played, and not your own vision and imagination, Then I rate your reveiw as thumbs down.This game is as fun and quirky as you might hope at a glance. I have not seen any crashes at all yet despite what some are saying. The game is open world/sandbox in design, thankfully (something FTL wasn't i might add), you control all the basics of crew assignements, trading, intersteller navigating, and of course your ship. You only control them in broad terms however, so I find the game a more casual, and light hearted approach, and I think that suits this games design and style. You wont find to much micromangement, but enough to satisfy a moderate amount of Compulsive Disorder I think. It feels like they have some good balance at its present stage in development and great vision for its future stages.If you wanna accelerate the pace and go pick a fight, you can.Wanna settle down and have a snack whilst slowly zipping from one trade stop to another, you can.Getting bored watching your ship move around and wanna speed things up ? you can.Dont like the way your medic is eyeballing you during your physical, and wanna fire him ? you can ! (there is no physical exams in the game by the way) *phew*In short what I like most about this game is the open ended/sandbox playstyle. Its a fun and playful game, and you can get an excellent and complete taste of the game even in its early access stage. I found my initial playthrough was surprisingly fun, and i left feeling quite excited for this games future potential.I would emphatically recommend this game for its low price, in fact, once its fleshed out in the future, I would pay even more. Its what 12 bucks or something ? Sheesh stop reading these reveiws and buy it, i think most will be quite positively surprised."
