76561198043985256,Not Recommended,320340,17144961,"Posted: 20 July, 2015",all,VGAstudent,"Before the game crashed all the time? It was like this...Honestly? The game Cosmonautica is quite entertaining for hours of micromanagement fun. I have been REALLY enjoying the replayability of the game, chosing which ship I want to fly for different types of weapons and crew capabilities! Hiring and firing, losing cargo, losing crew, losing patience when they rant and rave about no bathtubs and they stink in zero g inside a spacesuit they haven't changed in a week.Very cute, and quite a bit of fun!!...but now, since the developers had their hopes on a graphics engine fall through, it's not our problem to worry about, but rather the graphics engine developer to worry about, they're the one's with the history that left many computer users without graphics."
,Recommended,320340,17402595,"Posted: 5 August, 2015",all,Strabo1980,"I can't in good conscience recommend a ""finished"" game that has such a huge stability issue.To be clear, the gameplay itself is enjoyable if a bit repetitive. You sail across different galaxies transporting various goods, passengers, while occasionally (or quite often if you decide to become a pirate/warship) fighting other ships for missions/loot.So, gameplay aside, this Not Recommended is more to do with the fact that you can't play the game for any real length of time. It crashes, A LOT, every half hour or so for me, sometimes more often. Thankfully (or perhaps because of this issue?) the game designers used an auto-save function that saves your game after every major (or minor) interaction, pretty much. It saves it before you enter battle, when you get to, and when you leave a space station. Which is pretty much all you do in this game.The game also has a bad habit of corrupting save files, making them unloadable. This happens rarely, but when you've put 10-12 hours into a game and all of a sudden you can't access it, it's frustrating to say the least.Bacially, unless you have a burning desire to support the developers and their company, I recommend you stay away from this game until such time as they've fixed the game crash issues, or pick the game up at a deep discount. And keep in mind that you only have 2 hours (as per Steams' refund policy) to determine wheather or not you want to keep the game, because chances are you won't get a refund from them past that mark no matter how horrible your game plays. Or doesn't play...EDIT: I went ahead and changed my review to recommended after giving the game another try. While the game did crash a couple times, it did not crash repeatedly minutes after starting. So, as stated above, the gameplay is solid, and now that the game is stable, I would recommend this game if you're into third person space adventure."
